{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"12492","heading":"Compliance reviews","label":"12492 Compliance reviews","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/stI/ch121/schIII/ptL/spt2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Codification, which directed the addition of this section to chapter 2 of subtitle N of title IV of the Violence Against Women Act of 1994 ( et seq.), was executed by adding this section to chapter 2 of subtitle N of title IV of the Violent Crime Control and Law Enforcement Act of 1994 to reflect the probable intent of Congress.Pub. L. 117–103, div. W, title VI, § 60234 U.S.C. 12491","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Effective DateSection not effective until Oct. 1 of the first fiscal year beginning after , see , set out as a note under , Commerce and Trade.Mar. 15, 2022section 4(a) of div. W of Pub. L. 117–103section 6851 of Title 15"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Regular compliance reviews","label":"a Regular compliance reviews","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fa%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"where possible, be incorporated into other existing compliance review processes of the appropriate agency, in consultation with the Gender-based Violence Prevention Office and Violence Against Women Act Director described in and any other relevant officials of the appropriate agency; andsection 12493 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fa%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a/1/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"compliance with requirements prohibiting the denial of assistance, tenancy, or occupancy rights on the basis of domestic violence, dating violence, sexual assault, or stalking;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a/1/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"compliance with confidentiality provisions set forth in ;section 12491(c)(4) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a/1/B/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"compliance with the notification requirements set forth in ;section 12491(d)(2) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iv","heading":null,"label":"iv","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a/1/B/iv","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fiv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"compliance with the provisions for accepting documentation set forth in ;section 12491(c) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"v","heading":null,"label":"v","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a/1/B/v","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"compliance with emergency transfer requirements set forth in ; andsection 12491(e) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"vi","heading":null,"label":"vi","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a/1/B/vi","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fvi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"compliance with the prohibition on retaliation set forth in .section 12494 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Frequency","label":"2 Frequency","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Each appropriate agency shall conduct the review described in paragraph (1) on a regular basis, as determined by the appropriate agency.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Regulations","label":"b Regulations","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/b/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fb%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"define standards of compliance under covered housing programs;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/b/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fb%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"include detailed reporting requirements, including the number of emergency transfers requested and granted, as well as the length of time needed to process emergency transfers; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/b/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fb%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"include standards for corrective action plans where compliance standards have not been met.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Consultation","label":"2 Consultation","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"individuals and organizations with expertise in the housing needs and experiences of victims of domestic violence, dating violence, sexual assault and stalking; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"individuals and organizations with expertise in the administration or management of covered housing programs, including industry stakeholders and public housing agencies.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Public disclosure","label":"c Public disclosure","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"includes an evaluation of each topic identified in subsection (a); and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12492/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs12492%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is made publicly available.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
